          <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mt-1">Source: Identity Theft Resource Center</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Table of Contents -->
    <nav class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-6 mb-10" aria-label="Table of contents">
      <h2 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 text-lg">Table of Contents</h2>
      <ol class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
        <li><a href="#isp-tracking" class="hover:text-blue-600 hover:underline">1. Your ISP is Logging and Selling Your Browsing History</a></li>
        <li><a href="#government" class="hover:text-blue-600 hover:underline">2. Government Surveillance is Expanding (Yes, Even in Democracies)</a></li>
        <li><a href="#public-wifi" class="hover:text-blue-600 hover:underline">3. Public WiFi is a Security Nightmare</a></li>
        <li><a href="#geo-restrictions" class="hover:text-blue-600 hover:underline">4. Content is Being Censored and Geo-Blocked</a></li>
        <li><a href="#advertisers" class="hover:text-blue-600 hover:underline">5. Advertisers Track Your Every Move</a></li>
        <li><a href="#work-remote" class="hover:text-blue-600 hover:underline">6. Remote Work Requires Secure Connections</a></li>
