    <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">

      <section id="isp-tracking" class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">1. Your ISP is Logging and Selling Your Browsing History</h2>

        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          In 2017, the US Congress repealed FCC privacy rules that prevented ISPs from selling your browsing history without consent. Since then, Comcast, Verizon, AT&T, and other ISPs have been <strong>legally logging and monetizing</strong> every website you visit.
        </p>

        <div class="bg-yellow-50 border-l-4 border-yellow-500 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">What Your ISP Knows About You</h3>
