            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-red-600 font-bold">‚Ä¢</span>
              <span>Every website you visit (even with HTTPS, they see the domain)</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-red-600 font-bold">‚Ä¢</span>
              <span>When you visit each site and for how long</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-red-600 font-bold">‚Ä¢</span>
              <span>Your physical location (via IP address geolocation)</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-red-600 font-bold">‚Ä¢</span>
              <span>All connected devices in your home</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-red-600 font-bold">‚Ä¢</span>
              <span>Your search queries (if you use your ISP's DNS servers)</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          This data is sold to advertisers, data brokers, and third parties without your explicit consent. Even "incognito mode" doesn't help‚Äîyour ISP still sees everything.
        </p>

        <div class="bg-green-50 border-l-4 border-green-600 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">‚úÖ How a VPN Stops ISP Tracking</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            With a VPN, your ISP only sees encrypted traffic going to a single destination (the VPN server). They can't see which websites you visit, what you search for, or what you download. All they know is "this user is connected to a VPN"‚Äîthat's it.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="government" class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">2. Government Surveillance is Expanding (Yes, Even in Democracies)</h2>

        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          The Snowden revelations exposed mass surveillance programs in the US (PRISM), UK (Tempora), and allied countries. Despite public outrage, these programs have only <strong>expanded</strong> in scope.
        </p>

        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-6">
          <div class="bg-red-50 rounded-lg p-6">
            <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">
              <span class="text-2xl">üá∫üá∏</span>
              United States (5 Eyes)
            </h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-3">
              The NSA collects internet traffic under Section 702 of FISA. ISPs are legally required to provide bulk data to intelligence agencies. The PATRIOT Act and CLOUD Act allow warrantless data requests.
            </p>
            <span class="text-xs bg-red-100 text-red-800 px-2 py-1 rounded font-semibold">HIGH SURVEILLANCE</span>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-orange-50 rounded-lg p-6">
            <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">
              <span class="text-2xl">üá¨üáß</span>
              United Kingdom (5 Eyes)
            </h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-3">
              The Investigatory Powers Act (2016) requires ISPs to keep browsing histories for 12 months and grants government access without warrants. Often called the "Snooper's Charter."
            </p>
            <span class="text-xs bg-red-100 text-red-800 px-2 py-1 rounded font-semibold">HIGH SURVEILLANCE</span>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-yellow-50 rounded-lg p-6">
            <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">
              <span class="text-2xl">üá™üá∫</span>
              European Union
            </h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-3">
              GDPR provides strong privacy protections, but individual countries like France and Germany have data retention laws. The EU is debating "chat control" legislation to scan encrypted messages.
            </p>
            <span class="text-xs bg-yellow-100 text-yellow-800 px-2 py-1 rounded font-semibold">MODERATE SURVEILLANCE</span>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-green-50 rounded-lg p-6">
            <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">
              <span class="text-2xl">üá®üá≠</span>
              Switzerland
            </h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-3">
              Strong constitutional privacy protections. Not part of EU or 14 Eyes alliance. Courts require warrants for surveillance. Why ProtonVPN and Mullvad choose Swiss/Swedish jurisdictions.
            </p>
            <span class="text-xs bg-green-100 text-green-800 px-2 py-1 rounded font-semibold">LOW SURVEILLANCE</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-blue-50 border-l-4 border-blue-600 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">What About "I Have Nothing to Hide"?</h3>
